      "updated": 1773732272529,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "First layer is input layer\nHidden layer with non linear RBF activation fun\nLinear output layer\nDistance from cluster center is usually computed using\necludion distance.\nThe most commonly used RBF fun is gaussian fun\nThe output is weighted sum of hidden layers\n\nAdvantages:\n    1. Suitable for problems where the target fun is highly\n      complex",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "First layer is input layer\nHidden layer with non linear RBF activation fun\nLinear output layer\nDistance from cluster center is usually computed using\necludion distance.\nThe most commonly used RBF fun is gaussian fun\nThe output is weighted sum of hidden layers\n\nAdvantages:\n    1. Suitable for problems where the target fun is highly\n      complex",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
